ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, it gives a good introduction to Hilbert space, Banach space, LCS, and then Banach algebra.
I would recommend this course, but it is a very large workload.
Yes, it's a good course that covers many important topics.
It's a good survey of the various kinds of spaces arising in functional analysis.

Yes, would strongly recommend, but only to someone who had previously taken a class in measure theory and ideally some commutative algebra. The stated "prerequisites" are less stringent than the prerequisites in practice.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It helps me prepare my qualify exam and also get more insight into normed space
I understood many concepts that are important for my research, and learned how to use them.
The C*-algebra material will probably be important in my research some day.
functional analysis will be essential to me in my dissertation/research, and this class was a good grounding in the subject.
